content.text:
All 8 tests pass.

**Root cause:** The 500 mock was correctly triggering an `OrgApiError` inside the `_authed` route loader, but `_authed` has no `errorComponent`. TanStack Router falls back to its built-in default error UI ("Something went wrong!" with a "Hide Error" button) rather than bubbling to the root route's `errorComponent`. So `RootError` (with `data-testid="root-error"`) never rendered.

**Fix:** Set `defaultErrorComponent: RootError` on the router in `src/router.tsx`, so any route without its own `errorComponent` uses our `RootError` by default.

```14:29:apps/org-next/src/router.tsx
export const getRouter = () => {
  const rqContext = {
    queryClient: new QueryClient(),
  };

  const router = createRouter({
    context: {
      ...rqContext,
    },
    defaultErrorComponent: RootError,
    defaultPreload: "intent",
    routeTree,
  });
```

